# ROAM Codebase Rules

## Stack
- React Native + Expo 55 + Expo Router (file-based routing in app/)
- Supabase (auth, Postgres, edge functions, Realtime)
- Zustand (state management in lib/store.ts)
- RevenueCat (subscriptions)
- TypeScript strict mode

## Design System (lib/constants.ts) — NON-NEGOTIABLE
- Colors: bg=#080F0A, sage=#7CAF8A, cream=#F5EDD8, coral=#E8614A, gold=#C9A84C
- Fonts: Cormorant Garamond Bold (headers), DM Sans (body), DM Mono (labels)
- Icons: lucide-react-native ONLY. strokeWidth={2}, size={20} default.
- Dark-only UI. No light mode. No emojis anywhere.
- Use COLORS/FONTS/SPACING/RADIUS constants — NEVER hardcode values.

## Architecture
- All AI calls: supabase/functions/claude-proxy/ — NEVER call Anthropic directly from client
- All flight links: Skyscanner affiliate (no flight API, amadeus is dead)
- All hotel links: Booking.com affiliate (https://www.booking.com/search.html?ss=[dest]&aid=[AID])
- All activity links: GetYourGuide affiliate
- Free tier: 1 trip/month, enforced server-side in edge function
- Pro tier: unlimited, managed via RevenueCat
- Guest mode: anonymous auth + 1 trip ever

## Key Files
- lib/claude.ts — System prompt, callClaude(), buildTripPrompt(), generateItinerary()
- lib/store.ts — Zustand store (session, trips, isPro, currency, travelProfile)
- lib/constants.ts — COLORS, FONTS, SPACING, RADIUS, DESTINATIONS
- lib/types/itinerary.ts — Itinerary type + parseItinerary() runtime validator
- lib/flights.ts — Airport codes, home airport, Skyscanner affiliate links
- lib/booking-links.ts — Affiliate deep links (Booking, Skyscanner, GYG, SafetyWing, Airalo)
- lib/pro-gate.ts — Feature gating (free vs pro)
- lib/revenue-cat.ts — RevenueCat init, purchase, restore
- supabase/functions/claude-proxy/index.ts — Rate-limited AI proxy with JWT auth

## Code Standards
- Immutability always — never mutate, return new objects
- Files: 200-400 lines typical, 800 max
- Functions: <50 lines
- Nesting: <4 levels deep
- useCallback for handlers, useMemo for computed values
- Haptic feedback on all user interactions (lib/haptics.ts)
- Loading state on every async action
- User-facing error message on every failure
- Handle errors explicitly — never silently swallow

## Conventions
- Conventional commits: type(scope): description
- Types: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, test, chore
- All Supabase tables use RLS with auth.uid() ownership checks
- Edge functions use Deno.env.get() for secrets
- Hooks MUST be declared before any conditional early returns (React Rules of Hooks)

## Testing
- npx tsc --noEmit — must pass after every change
- npx expo export --platform web — must pass before deploy
- Test with diverse destinations: Tokyo, Marrakech, Bali, Reykjavik, Oaxaca

## NEVER
- Use emojis in UI code
- Put API keys in client code (except Supabase anon key, Google Places)
- Call Anthropic API directly from client
- Use WITH CHECK (true) in RLS policies on sensitive tables
- Ship console.log with sensitive data
- Use any icon library other than lucide-react-native
- Hardcode hex colors, font families, or spacing values
- Mutate state — always create new objects
- Reference amadeus anywhere — it is dead and removed
